-- Slovak Parties Clash Over Economy Ministry Nomination, Hospodarske Reports
-- Radoslav Tomek
-- 2010-06-28T06:41:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/slovak-parties-clash-over-economy-ministry-nomination-hospodarske-reports.html

          
          
             Slovak negotiations within a four-
party coalition about the division of ministries in a new
cabinet have been stalled over the nomination of the economy
minister,  Hospodarske Noviny  reported.  
 Christian Democrats Chairman  Jan Figel  wants the position
for himself, he told the newspaper based in the Slovak capital,
Bratislava. Freedom and Solidarity is also interested in the
post, Hospodarske said, citing party Vice Chairman Juraj Miskov.  
 The two parties have been negotiating with SDKU and Most-
Hid about forming a four-way cabinet led by SDKU leader  Iveta Radicova . Talks will continue today, Hospodarske said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
